The paper focuses on the interpretability of results from a convolutional neural network for the classification of oesophageal tissue. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a novel deep learning method, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of attention maps, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper involves the classification of medical images, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
